B.Gl=new A.uD("Irritant Contact Dermatitis","The clinical picture strongly suggests irritant contact dermatitis (ICD). Key features are the direct correlation with a new occupational irritant (frequent hand-washing), ill-defined borders, vesicles on an erythematous base, and excoriation from pruritus. Unlike allergic contact dermatitis, ICD does not require prior sensitisation \u2014 repeated exposure to an irritant disrupts the skin barrier directly. Management centres on removing the trigger and restoring the barrier with emollients and a short course of topical steroid.",B.K0,"Psoriasis would present with well-demarcated, silvery-scaled plaques on extensor surfaces \u2014 the opposite pattern to this case. Atopic eczema shares flexural distribution but typically has a personal or family atopy history.")
B.Iw=s(["contact-dermatitis","inflammatory","occupational","topical-steroids"],t.s)
B.DA=new A.ls("case_001","Itchy rash on forearm",B.jq,"A 26-year-old nurse presents with a 5-day history of an itchy, erythematous rash on the flexural surface of the right forearm. No previous skin conditions. Reports increased hand-washing frequency over the past month due to a new ward placement.","No known drug allergies. No personal or family history of atopy. First episode. Not on any regular medications.","assets/images/case_001_v2.png",B.Ie,B.Jo,B.IN,B.Gl,B.Iw,"Common in healthcare workers due to repeated glove use and hand hygiene.")
B.MW=new A.cN("o2_1","Silvery-white scale",!0)
