B.Gj=new A.uD("Atopic Eczema","Atopic eczema in infants typically presents with a red, dry, itchy rash on the face (cheeks) and extensor surfaces of the limbs. The positive family history (father affected) and the classic distribution support the diagnosis.",B.IV,"Seborrhoeic dermatitis in infants (cradle cap) usually affects the scalp and flexures, and is typically not as itchy as atopic eczema.")
